JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 796
EP  - 799
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a response to an earlier article in ?Academy of Management Review? titled ?Ecocentric Management for a Risk Society,? by Paul Shrivastava. The author takes issue with Shrivastava's claim that technological and ecological risk will take the place of product orientations in a post industrial world. The author argues that instead of replacing product orientation, environmental and risk considerations will influence product orientation. A competing paradigm might cause industry to dismiss those environmental and risk factors that should be a part of product management.
