JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 961
EP  - 985
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Increasingly ecologists have recognized the importance of sudden and unexpected changes in the natural environment?often called ?surprises.? Organizational scholars have not developed a theory of how to avoid ecological surprise. This article suggests one way to develop such a theory. Using ecology, systems analysis, and a historical comparison of four communities, the article concludes that organizing and managing natural resources in part as community property can play a central role in avoiding surprises.
